<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
  Hilton/Halton Falls "Living Wall" — Framed Video Widget
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  A single drop-in block: your looping conservation-area video plays through
  the window of the purple wood/vine picture frame, with the frame drawn on
  top so its leaves and edges overlap the footage naturally.

  Why this approach (not a single pre-composited video):
  Browsers do not reliably support real alpha-channel transparency in web
  video codecs in every environment. Instead this keeps the two assets
  separate — a plain rectangular looping video UNDER a transparent PNG frame
  ON TOP — positioned with exact percentage math so the video always lines
  up with the frame's inner window at any size. This is both more robust
  and far lighter (no wasted encoding of pixels the frame covers anyway).

  Files needed alongside this HTML:
    - halton-falls-active.webm   (primary loop, plays behind the frame)
    - halton-falls-active.mp4    (H.264 fallback)
    - halton-falls-active-poster.jpg (first paint / reduced-motion fallback)
    - frame-purple-vines.png     (the trimmed frame graphic, transparent bg)

  Drop-in usage: copy the <div id="hf-framed-wall"> block plus the <style>
  into the target page, in the Canadian Innovation Dimension section above
  the wetlands/boreal content.
-->
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<title>Halton Falls — Framed Living Wall (Preview)</title>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<style>
  #hf-framed-wall, #hf-framed-wall * { box-sizing: border-box; }

  #hf-framed-wall {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 900px;         /* adjust to taste for the CID section */
    margin: 0 auto;
    aspect-ratio: 1428 / 1078; /* native frame canvas ratio — keeps the
                                   video-to-frame alignment exact at any
                                   display size */
  }

  /* The video sits UNDER the frame, cropped/positioned to exactly fill
     the frame's inner window (computed from the frame PNG's true pixel
     geometry: window at 11.975% / 25.046% of the canvas, 67.017% wide,
     61.41% tall). */
  #hf-framed-wall .hf-video-window {
    position: absolute;
    left: 11.975%;
    top: 25.046%;
    width: 67.017%;
    height: 61.41%;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #0b1512; /* shown briefly before the poster/video paints */
    z-index: 1;
  }

  #hf-framed-wall .hf-video-window video,
  #hf-framed-wall .hf-video-window img.hf-poster {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 55%;
    display: block;
  }

  #hf-framed-wall .hf-poster { display: none; }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    #hf-framed-wall .hf-video-window video { display: none; }
    #hf-framed-wall .hf-poster { display: block !important; }
  }

  /* The frame graphic sits ON TOP, full-bleed over the whole component so
     its leaf overhang and wood edges render above the video seam. */
  #hf-framed-wall .hf-frame-art {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: 2;
    pointer-events: none; /* clicks pass through to whatever is beneath */
    user-select: none;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body style="margin:0; background:#f4f1ea; padding:40px;">

<div id="hf-framed-wall" aria-label="Live looping footage of Halton Falls Conservation Area, Ontario, framed with a decorative purple wood and vine border">
  <div class="hf-video-window">
    <video
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="metadata"
      poster="halton-falls-active-poster.jpg"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      <source src="halton-falls-active.webm" type="video/webm" />
      <source src="halton-falls-active.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
    </video>
    <img class="hf-poster" src="halton-falls-active-poster.jpg" alt="" />
  </div>

  <img class="hf-frame-art" src="frame-purple-vines.png" alt="" />
</div>

</body>
</html>
